Cld is a stand-alone C++ library for the Chromium Compact Language Detector. Used mainly for detecting the language
of text. Origin: http://mzsanford.com/blog/introducing-libcld/

Some tools may be required before installing.
On CentOS run:
sudo yum install git dialog automake autoconf libtool

To install it from the external source:

1. git clone http://github.com/mzsanford/cld.git
2. cd cld
3. ./configure && make
4. make check # test early. Test often.
5. sudo make install

To install it from local source
1. Copy cld from the same source where CVSummaryExtractor resides
2. cd cld
3. ./configure && make
4. make check # test early. Test often.
5. sudo make install
